   "body" : "Following an [IRC conversation today](http://www.erisian.com.au/bitcoin-core-dev/log-2021-02-13.html#l-325), this patch proposes to persist `CLIENT_VERSION` to the `settings.json` file on shutdown.\r\n\r\nDoing so may be useful, for example, to detect if the user upgraded with code like\r\n```cpp\r\nif (CLIENT_VERSION > chain.getRwSetting(\"version\"))\r\n```\r\nto take various actions.\r\n\r\nReviewers, this patch can be tested manually by loading `<datadir>/signet/settings.json`, starting and stopping signet, and watching the file be updated. One can also manually edit the setting and verify that the version is updated on shutdown.\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"version\": 219900,\r\n    \"wallet\": [\r\n        \"\"\r\n    ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
